12/05/2003
ANTALYA, Turkey -- Turkey, Bulgaria and Romania signed a memorandum on co-operation in the fight against terrorism on Sunday (11 May). Meeting in the resort town of Antalya, interior ministers of the three countries discussed common security problems and ways to resolve them through co-operation. They also reached a consensus on sharing information and facilities related to consular and visa activities. (Anadolu Agency - 11/05/03)
